---
layout: layouts/element.njk
title: "iframe"
description: "The iframe element embeds external content with responsive containers and security best practices for third-party integrations."
elementName: iframe
category: native
nativeGroup: Embedded
currentPath: /docs/elements/native/iframe/
permalink: /docs/elements/native/iframe/
---

{% set basicIframeCode %}<iframe src="page.html" title="Descriptive title"></iframe>{% endset %}

{% set borderedIframeCode %}<iframe class="bordered" src="page.html" title="..."></iframe>{% endset %}

{% set responsiveEmbedCode %}<section class="embed-responsive">
  <iframe
    src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/VIDEO_ID"
    title="Video title"
    allowfullscreen>
  </iframe>
</section>{% endset %}

{% set ratio4x3Code %}<section class="embed-responsive ratio-4x3">
  <iframe src="..." title="..."></iframe>
</section>{% endset %}

{% set sandboxCode %}<!-- Most restrictive: no scripts, forms, or same-origin access -->
<iframe sandbox src="..." title="..."></iframe>

<!-- Allow scripts only -->
<iframe sandbox="allow-scripts" src="..." title="..."></iframe>

<!-- Common for video embeds -->
<iframe
  sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin"
  src="..."
  title="...">
</iframe>

<!-- For forms -->
<iframe
  sandbox="allow-forms allow-scripts allow-same-origin"
  src="..."
  title="...">
</iframe>{% endset %}

{% set cspCode %}<!-- HTTP header -->
Content-Security-Policy: frame-src 'self' https://www.youtube.com https://player.vimeo.com;

<!-- Meta tag -->
<meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy"
      content="frame-src 'self' https://www.youtube.com;">{% endset %}

{% set referrerCode %}<iframe
  referrerpolicy="no-referrer"
  src="..."
  title="...">
</iframe>{% endset %}

{% set youtubeCode %}<section class="embed-responsive">
  <iframe
    src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/dQw4w9WgXcQ"
    title="YouTube video player"
    allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
    allowfullscreen
    loading="lazy">
  </iframe>
</section>{% endset %}

{% set mapCode %}<section class="embed-responsive ratio-4x3">
  <iframe
    src="https://www.openstreetmap.org/export/embed.html?bbox=..."
    title="Map showing office location"
    loading="lazy">
  </iframe>
</section>{% endset %}

{% set titleExamplesCode %}<!-- Good: descriptive title -->
<iframe
  src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/..."
  title="Introduction to Web Accessibility - Tutorial Video">
</iframe>

<!-- Bad: generic or missing title -->
<iframe src="..."></iframe>
<iframe src="..." title="iframe"></iframe>{% endset %}

{% set lazyLoadCode %}<iframe
  src="..."
  title="..."
  loading="lazy">
</iframe>{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;iframe&gt;</code> element embeds another HTML document within the current page. VB removes default borders, provides variant classes for visual style, and offers responsive wrapper classes for common aspect ratios.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Video embeds:</strong> YouTube, Vimeo, and other video platforms</li>
      <li><strong>Maps:</strong> Google Maps, OpenStreetMap embeds</li>
      <li><strong>Social widgets:</strong> Twitter timelines, social posts</li>
      <li><strong>Payment forms:</strong> Stripe, PayPal checkout</li>
      <li><strong>Third-party tools:</strong> Calendars, forms, surveys</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>When to Use Other Elements</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Use <a href="/docs/elements/native/video/"><code>&lt;video&gt;</code></a> for self-hosted video files</li>
      <li>Use <a href="/docs/elements/native/audio/"><code>&lt;audio&gt;</code></a> for self-hosted audio</li>
      <li>Use <a href="/docs/elements/native/dialog/"><code>&lt;dialog&gt;</code></a> for modal content on your own page</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Variants</h2>
    <p>VB removes the default iframe border and provides variant classes for visual style.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/iframe-examples.html" url="iframe-examples.html" title="Iframe variants" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic iframe">{{ basicIframeCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Bordered iframe">{{ borderedIframeCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Class</th><th>Effect</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>(default)</td><td>No border, block display, max-width 100%</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>.bordered</code></td><td>Subtle border with rounded corners</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>.rounded</code></td><td>Medium border radius, overflow hidden</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>.full</code></td><td>100% container width</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>.fixed</code></td><td>100% width, fixed 400px height</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Responsive Embeds</h2>
    <p>Wrap an iframe in an <code>.embed-responsive</code> container to maintain aspect ratio while filling available width. The iframe stretches to fill the container via absolute positioning.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/iframe-responsive.html" url="iframe-responsive.html" title="Responsive embed ratios" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="16:9 responsive embed">{{ responsiveEmbedCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="4:3 aspect ratio embed">{{ ratio4x3Code | escape }}</code-block>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Wrapper Class</th><th>Aspect Ratio</th><th>Use Case</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>.embed-responsive</code></td><td>16:9</td><td>YouTube, Vimeo, most video</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>.ratio-4x3</code></td><td>4:3</td><td>Classic presentations, some maps</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>.ratio-1x1</code></td><td>1:1</td><td>Instagram embeds, square widgets</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>.ratio-21x9</code></td><td>21:9</td><td>Cinematic video, ultrawide content</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Live Embeds</h2>
    <p>Real-world embed examples showing YouTube video and OpenStreetMap.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/iframe-live-embeds.html" url="iframe-live-embeds.html" title="Live embed examples" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="YouTube video embed">{{ youtubeCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="OpenStreetMap embed">{{ mapCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <p><strong>Privacy note:</strong> Use <code>youtube-nocookie.com</code> instead of <code>youtube.com</code> for privacy-enhanced mode that doesn't set tracking cookies until the user plays the video.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Security</h2>

    <h3>The sandbox Attribute</h3>
    <p>Restricts iframe capabilities. Start with an empty value (most restrictive) and add permissions as needed.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Sandbox attribute examples">{{ sandboxCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Sandbox Value</th><th>Allows</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>allow-scripts</code></td><td>JavaScript execution</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>allow-same-origin</code></td><td>Treat content as same origin</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>allow-forms</code></td><td>Form submission</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>allow-popups</code></td><td>Open new windows/tabs</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>allow-modals</code></td><td>Modal dialogs (alert, confirm)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>allow-downloads</code></td><td>Downloading files</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Content Security Policy</h3>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Content Security Policy">{{ cspCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Referrer Policy</h3>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Referrer policy">{{ referrerCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>

    <h3>Title Attribute</h3>
    <p>Every iframe <strong>must</strong> have a <code>title</code> attribute that describes its content for screen readers.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Title attribute examples">{{ titleExamplesCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Lazy Loading</h3>
    <p>Defer loading of below-the-fold iframes for better performance.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Lazy loading iframe">{{ lazyLoadCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Best Practices</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Always provide a descriptive <code>title</code> attribute</li>
      <li>Use <code>loading="lazy"</code> for below-the-fold embeds</li>
      <li>Ensure embedded content is itself accessible</li>
      <li>Provide alternative content for critical information</li>
      <li>Consider that some users block third-party content</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Reference</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Selector</th><th>Properties</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>iframe</code></td><td><code>display: block; border: none; max-inline-size: 100%;</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>iframe.full</code></td><td><code>inline-size: 100%;</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>iframe.fixed</code></td><td><code>inline-size: 100%; block-size: 400px;</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>iframe.rounded</code></td><td><code>border-radius: var(--radius-m); overflow: hidden;</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>iframe.bordered</code></td><td><code>border; border-radius;</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>.embed-responsive</code></td><td><code>position: relative; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>.embed-responsive > iframe</code></td><td><code>position: absolute; inset: 0; 100% width/height;</code></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

